         'mango': 56,
         'plum': 10}

amount=fruits.values()

plt.bar(names, amount, color='orange')
plt.title('fruit distribution')
plt.xlabel('fruit name')
plt.ylabel('no of fruits')
plt.show()

In [28]:
# customizing scatterplot

x = np.array([1,2,3,4,5])
y1 = np.array([7,8,9,10,11])
y2 = np.array([3,6,9,12,15])

plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))

plt.scatter(x,y1, marker='1', s=200)
plt.scatter(x,y2)

plt.legend(['a','b'])
plt.title('x vs y1 and y2')
plt.xlabel('x-axis->')
plt.ylabel('y-axis->')

plt.show()

In [108]:
pl= ['Java', 'Python', 'PHP', 'JavaScript', 'C#', 'C++']
pop = [22.2, 17.6, 8.8, 8, 7.7, 6.7]
p = [22.2, 17.6, 8.8, 8, 7.7, 6.7]
colors=['red','green','blue','brown','pink','violet']
plt.bar(pl,pop, color=colors)
for pl, pop, p in zip(pl, pop, p):
   plt.text(pl, pop, p)
plt.show()
